    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="416"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 156.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 29, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 12th instant, No. 92, and
                    its accompanying copy of a note which you addressed to Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys upon
                    the subject of the President’s proclamations, which were transmitted to you with
                    my instruction, No. 112, has been received and is approved.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                        >&amp;</hi>c., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
